File Organization

Always maintain a clean and scalable project structure.

Before creating a new file

Check whether:

Similar functionality already exists.
The code can be added to an existing file.
A reusable component already exists.

Do not create files unnecessarily.

File Placement

Place files according to their responsibility.

Examples:

Screens inside feature folders.
Reusable widgets inside widgets folders.
Models inside models folders.
Services inside services folders.
Repositories inside repositories folders.
Providers inside providers folders.

Never place unrelated code in the same file.

File Size Guidelines

Prefer small and maintainable files.

Guidelines:

Widgets should have a single responsibility.
Large screens should be split into smaller widgets.
Avoid files exceeding roughly 300-500 lines unless justified.
Extract repeated UI into reusable widgets.

Do not over-engineer.

Balance readability and maintainability.

Import Rules
Remove unused imports.
Prefer package imports over deep relative imports when appropriate.
Keep imports organized.
Avoid circular dependencies.
Localization & Translations

The application must be fully localization-ready.

No Hardcoded User-Facing Text

Never introduce hardcoded UI strings such as:

Text('Save')
Text('Delete')
Text('Settings')

Instead use the project's localization system.

Example:

context.l10n.save
context.l10n.delete
context.l10n.settings
When Adding New Text

Whenever a new user-facing text is introduced:

Add the translation key.
Add Arabic translation.
Add English translation.
Update generated localization files if required.
Replace hardcoded strings with localization references.

Do not leave untranslated text behind.

Translation Consistency

Before creating a new translation key:

Search existing localization files.
Reuse existing keys whenever possible.
Avoid duplicate keys with different names.

Example:

Bad:

save
save_button
save_changes

Good:

save

Reuse existing translations.

RTL Support

Every new screen must be checked for:

Arabic layout compatibility.
RTL alignment.
RTL navigation flow.
Text overflow in Arabic.
Responsive behavior.

Do not assume LTR layouts.

UI Consistency

Before creating:

Colors
Typography
Padding
Border radius
Icons

Check existing design system first.

Reuse:

AppColors
AppTextStyles
Existing shared widgets

Avoid duplicate design definitions.

Final Verification

Before completing any task verify:

No hardcoded user-facing text exists.
All new text is translated.
File placement follows project structure.
No duplicate widgets were introduced.
No unnecessary files were created.
RTL layout still works correctly.
